    "_postman_id": "24997207-f71d-414e-8273-b6dec85be3f4",
    "name": "AutomationExcersice API tests",
    "description": "# AutomationExercise API Test Collection\n\nA comprehensive API test suite for automationexercise.com built as part of a QA Engineering portfolio project.\n\n## What This Collection Covers\n\nThis collection tests the core API endpoints of the AutomationExercise e-commerce application including user authentication, account management and product data retrieval.\n\n## Endpoints Tested\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| GET | /api/productsList | Retrieve all products |\n| GET | /api/brandsList | Retrieve all brands |\n| POST | /api/verifyLogin | Authenticate a user |\n| POST | /api/verifyLogin | Login with invalid credentials |\n| POST | /api/verifyLogin | Login with missing parameters |\n| POST | /api/createAccount | Register a new user account |\n| POST | /api/createAccount | Duplicate email edge case |\n| DELETE | /api/deleteAccount | Delete an existing account |\n| DELETE | /api/deleteAccount | Delete non-existent account edge case |\n\n## Test Strategy\n\nEach request includes multiple assertions covering:\n\n- HTTP status codes\n    \n- Response time thresholds (under 3000ms)\n    \n- Response body structure and data types\n    \n- Field validation and uniqueness checks\n    \n- Security checks (no sensitive data exposed)\n    \n- Edge cases and negative scenarios\n    \n- Environment variable management\n    \n\n## Tools & Environment\n\n- Tool: Postman\n    \n- Language: JavaScript (Postman test scripts)\n    \n- API Type: REST\n    \n- Authentication: form-data credentials\n    \n\n## Bugs Discovered During Testing\n\n- BUG-008: API returns incorrect Content-Type header (text/html instead of application/json)\n    \n- BUG-009: API exposes internal Django framework details on 404 responses\n    \n\n## Author\n\nGeorgina Adzorgenu  \nQA Engineering Portfolio Project — April 2026",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "8712280"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "https://automationexercise.com/api/productsList",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"Response time is under 3000ms\", () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(3000);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"Response body is not empty\", () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.not.be.empty;",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"Response contains products array\", () => {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json.products).to.be.an(\"array\");",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"Products list is not empty\", () => {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json.products.length).to.be.above(0);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"Each product has id, name and price\", () => {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    json.products.forEach((product) => {",
              "        pm.expect(product).to.have.property(\"id\");",
              "        pm.expect(product).to.have.property(\"name\");",
              "        pm.expect(product).to.have.property(\"price\");",
              "    });",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"Content-Type is text/html\", () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get(\"Content-Type\")).to.include(\"text/html\");",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"All product IDs are unique\", () => {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    const ids = json.products.map(p => p.id);",
              "    const uniqueIds = [...new Set(ids)];",
              "    pm.expect(ids.length).to.equal(uniqueIds.length);",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
